## Design notes

| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Data structure** | `Map<IP, number[]>` — timestamps kept in ascending order so `pruneExpired` is an O(k) prefix-scan, not a sort. |
| **Prune trigger** | On every request (to count accurately) **and** on a 60-second background sweep (to reclaim memory for silent IPs). |
| **`retryAfter` value** | `ceil((oldestTimestamp + windowMs) − now) / 1000` — tells the client the exact moment one slot opens, not an arbitrary constant. |
| **`X-RateLimit-Reset`** | Uses `timestamps[0]` (the oldest surviving timestamp) for the same reason. |
| **Process-exit safety** | `cleanupInterval.unref()` prevents the timer from blocking exit; `close()` provides an explicit teardown hook for graceful-shutdown handlers. |
| **No dependencies** | Pure Node.js — no `redis`, no `ioredis`, no `express-rate-limit`. Suitable for single-process deployments; for multi-instance/cluster deployments, replace the `Map` with a shared Redis store (e.g. using a sorted set per IP and `ZREMRANGEBYSCORE` + `ZCARD`). |

